The paper deals with learning from demonstrations for a robot to perform a task efficiently. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sparse movement primitive parameters, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper presents real robot experiments, which can be considered as a system and control (cs.SY) problem.
